    Looking for my.chapman.edu?



My.chapman.edu was recently replaced by a more modern version of the technology that powers the Chapman University campus. The new system is more secure, mobile friendly, and easier to use, but offers the same functionality as my.chapman.edu.
New and continuing students can get to the new site by going to studentcenter.chapman.edu in any browser or by using the 'paw' dropdown from any page on chapman.edu and selecting "Student Center."
For more information, please visit the Student Center Resource Page.





Toggle Section





                                                Faculty/Advisor Center

                                            

Faculty/Advisor center can still be found in its current location, which is to navigate to working.chapman.edu and click on the Faculty/Advisor Center link.
You can get to working.chapman.edu by: 

Entering the url in any browser
Clicking on the Working@chapman link through the paw login menu from any page on www.chapman.edu

For more information, please visit the Faculty/Advisor Center Resource Page.






                                                Student Center

                                            

Students can get to the new site by going to studentcenter.chapman.edu in any browser or by using the 'paw' dropdown from any page on chapman.edu and selecting "Student Center."
For more information, please visit the Student Center Resource Page.






                                                Public Class Search

                                            

Please visit our Public Class Search to find information about classes for past, current or upcoming terms.
For current Chapman students, to view your own class registration, the Chapman Student Center is the primary tool to search for open classes and register for them, and will require a Chapman network userid to login.
 






                                                Need Additional Support?

                                            

Have additional support questions? 
Chapman's IS&T Service Desk is on hand to provide additional support as needed on this topic. Please contact the service desk at your convenience.
